body:
Say I have a simple specification:

``` yaml
swagger: '2.0'
info:
  title: Validation Issue
  description: Endpoints
  version: 0.0.1
basePath: /v1
consumes:
  - application/json
produces:
  - application/json

paths:
  /events:
    post:
      parameters:
        - name: event
          in: body
          description: Event to post
          required: true
          schema:
            $ref: '#/definitions/Event'
      responses:
        '201':
          $ref: '#/responses/Created'

definitions:
  Event:
    type: string

responses:
  CreatedEventResponse:
    description: Successfully created an event
    schema:
      $ref: '#/definitions/Event'

```

A Validate method is not generated for the Event model; however, it is referenced in the BindRequest method for the path that uses it, even though I did not specify validation i.e. body.Validate(route.Formats).

Generated models/event.go

``` go
package models

// This file was generated by the swagger tool.
// Editing this file might prove futile when you re-run the swagger generate command

/*Event Event event

swagger:model Event
*/
type Event string
```

Generated restapi/operations/post_events_parameters.go

``` go
package operations

// This file was generated by the swagger tool.
// Editing this file might prove futile when you re-run the swagger generate command

import (
    "net/http"

    "github.com/go-swagger/go-swagger/errors"
    "github.com/go-swagger/go-swagger/httpkit/middleware"

    "github.com/rossnanop/swagger-issue/models"
)

// NewPostEventsParams creates a new PostEventsParams object
// with the default values initialized.
func NewPostEventsParams() PostEventsParams {
    return PostEventsParams{}
}

// PostEventsParams contains all the bound params for the post events operation
// typically these are obtained from a http.Request
//
// swagger:parameters PostEvents
type PostEventsParams struct {
    /*Event to post
      Required: true
      In: body
    */
    Event models.Event
}

// BindRequest both binds and validates a request, it assumes that complex things implement a Validatable(strfmt.Registry) error interface
// for simple values it will use straight method calls
func (o *PostEventsParams) BindRequest(r *http.Request, route *middleware.MatchedRoute) error {
    var res []error

    var body models.Event
    if err := route.Consumer.Consume(r.Body, &body); err != nil {
        res = append(res, errors.NewParseError("event", "body", "", err))
    } else {
        if err := body.Validate(route.Formats); err != nil {
            res = append(res, err)
        }

        if len(res) == 0 {
            o.Event = body
        }
    }

    if len(res) > 0 {
        return errors.CompositeValidationError(res...)
    }
    return nil
}
```

The error generated is:

```
at line 42, file swagger-issue/restapi/operations/post_events_parameters.go body.Validate undefined (type models.Event has no field or method Validate)
```

I would recommend generating the validation method for all types to encourage proper validation of parameters; however, the swagger specification does not require it.
